reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is the 2nd WiFi extender I bought because I figured the other WiFi extender I bought just didn’t have enough distance. I live on the first floor and my security camera is on the 2nd floor on an outside window. I’ve tried everything to get my camera to have more signal and only a very small change. I thought it would provide my camera with all the bars. And it gave my camera one little tiny bar of wifi. I first set it up close to the router. Then I put it halfway so I plug it in the hallway. And now it is plugged on the 2nd floor in my neighbors front bedroom. And it’s just so frustrating because it does say wall penetration & it does say 10,000square feet. But the slim to none difference it has made on my security system I don’t think is worth the money. Big disappointment. I read all the good reviews and thought I’d give it a try. Idk what else to do. I will be returning unfortunately
